 to lure us to an ultimately incorrect syntactic construction. In the above example, "tunes" can function as either a noun or a verb, and when primed with the word "whistles," which can be either transitive or intransitive, we decide that "tunes" functions as a noun and attach it as a direct object, which ends up being incorrect.%0a%3c %0a%3c Some other examples of garden path sentences include:%0a%3c The old man the boat.%0a%3c The horse raced past the garden fell.%0a%3c Fat people eat accumulates.%0a%3c Mary gave the child the dog bit a bandaid.%0a%3c The man who hunts ducks out on weekends.%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
